data.enText: a unit for measuring the force of an electric current

data.chText: 有5 000伏电流通过的森严铁丝网
data.enText: a high-security fence with 5 000 volts passing through it

tr: a unit of potential equal to the potential difference between two points on a conductor carrying a current of 1 ampere when the power dissipated between the two points is 1 watt
equivalent to the potential difference across a resistance of 1 ohm when 1 ampere of current flows through it

value.def: A volt is a unit used to measure the force of an electric current.
